  • Classes

    Description
    AABB
    Represents an Axis-Aligned Bounding Box (AABB), commonly used in geometric calculations such as collision detection, spatial queries, and bounding volume hierarchies.
    CalcAreas
    This class provides methods to calculate property areas and manage changes in a graph structure of properties.
    Coordinates
    Represents a point in a 2D coordinate system.
    GraphStructure
    Represents a graph structure for managing and visualizing relationships between properties.
    Main
     
    OwnerGraphStructure
    Represents a graph structure to model relationships between property owners based on property adjacency.
    OwnerGraphStructure.PropertyPair
    Represents a pair of properties with associated owners.
    Property
    Represents a property with geographic and ownership details.
    PropFileReader
    A utility class for reading and parsing property data from a `.csv` file.
    Visualizer
    A visual representation of a graph of properties using JGraphT.
